5: Marchella! Lend your aid to Nimbus!
15:
Now that's what I'm talking about!
Some nice moves there, Marchella.
23:
You have a good set of eyes on you.
No doubt that's a product of all your
practice marching on the field!
31:
Well, I'm ready for more! Let's keep
at it!
35:
...And then Nimbus even praised me
for what I did!
40: I knew you would do a great job.
44:
Exploring the Kaleidoscope gets me
so fired up! It's like something out of
an adventure book!
47:
Say, Alk. Do you think I could cut it as
an adventurer?
52:
I mean, you have what it takes! You
don't need my approval.
54:
But, is that what you really want? To
become an adventurer?
60:
It's just... whenever I think about the
future, I get unsure. Like, is this really
the right path for me?
63:
I mean, first and foremost, I'm a
student at Voluntas!
65:
I should be focusing on finding work
as a mage after I graduate. That's
what my parents think I'm doing.
68:
But... I went and fell in love with
marching instead.
81:
No! It's great! It's just... things are
more complicated than that.
84:
Being an adventurer is fun! And so is
being a mage! But I absolutely LOVE
being in a marching band.
87:
But how can someone as uncertain
as me stand at the front of a band
and lead them?!
92:
So you've got stuff like that on your
mind too, huh.
96:
You mean, like everyone else? Am I
just that simple?
101:
No, no. That's not what I meant.
What you said really reminded me
of Stella, that's all.
104:
But I guess it makes sense.
Everyone's got their own worries.
114:
And I have no idea what the right
answer is.
119:
All right, I think that's about all the
ingredients we needed.
122:
Marchella said she liked your red
soup.
127:
Yeah, that's why I figured I should
make it again. She needs to get her
mind off things, and food can help
you do that.
131: You two must be Alk and Stella.
133:
We have something that requires
your attention. Come with us.
137: We should be okay to go.
142:
You need to stop associating with
Marchella. Otherwise, you'll regret it.
145:
Marchella? Seriously? I gotta admit, I
didn't see that coming.
148:
Um... What do you mean by
"associating," exactly?
151:
Huh? I, uh... You know what I mean!
Right, "adventurer"?
160:
So if you know what's good for you,
you'll give us back our no-good,
practice-skipping flake of a drum
major!
162:
Marchella hasn't come to practice
recently... She said she was going off
on a "journey to find herself" or
something.
164:
You're part of this... Putting all sorts
of distracting thoughts in her head.
This is an important time for us!
172:
Objection! Now wait just a minute
there, Elsie!
175:
A-hah! Our plan worked! We laid the
bait and she fell for it!
177:
H-hey! I don't appreciate being used
as bait.
182:
Why are making such a big deal of
this? I put in the paperwork for leave
from club activites!
185:
You didn't even say goodbye! You
just submitted the letter and
stopped showing up!
187:
You're just getting all flustered and
nervous before the big
performance. I bet nothing's even
wrong with you!
189:
H-hey, I'm actually really conflicted
here, okay?
192:
Oh? Well... If that's the case, then
fine. Whatever. We can get by
without you.
194:
You know why? Cause now that
you're gone, I get to be the drum
major in your place, just like I always
wanted.
196:
Now I can get all the glory, and you
can sit in the stands and watch, all
while sniveling like a big baby! Hah!
200:
You were the one who wanted to
find Marchella the MOST. Why are
you saying stuff like that?
203:
Wait, they're supposed to be
friends? Could have fooled me.
206: They look like they're having fun.
209:
Well, whatever. You're the only one
who can wrangle this bunch of
misfits anyway! We need you.
211:
So, respectfully, Drum Major... Pull
yourself together and lead us!
You're... our guiding star, after all.
215:
Sorry for getting you two involved in
this! Um, I think I'm going to be a bit
late coming over today, if that's
okay.
218:
No problem. We'll leave some of the
chicken tomato stew out for you.
